sentences: Donald Clark Osmond (born December 9, 1957) is an American singer, dancer, actor, television host, and former teen idol.
The Donny & Marie duo also released a series of top ten hits and gold albums and hosted a syndicated and Daytime Emmy Award–nominated 1998–2000 talk show.
Most recently, Donny & Marie retired from headlining an 11-year Las Vegas residency at the Flamingo Las Vegas (2008–2019).
He also hosted the game show Pyramid from 2002 to 2004.
Osmond was born on December 9, 1957, in Ogden, Utah, the seventh son of Olive May (née Davis; 1925–2004) and George Virl Osmond (1917–2007).
